<span id="freeTextContainer7175428119808821379">Writing this from the middle of the Brooklyn Bridge! I give the author 5 stars for his research, but ultimately I found the subject matter somewhat ordinary and slow. Plus, too much of the book was taken up with highly technical descriptions of how the bridge was constructed and mundane details of bureaucracy. If a large chunk of the lengthy material had been cut down, it probably would have made for a more compelling story. </span>

